[10.955033, "o", "\r\u001b[Kdemo=# \u001b[2m/\u001b[0mrpg\r\u001b[11C\u001b[?2004l\r\n\r\n\u001b[38;5;13m\u001b[1m  ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\r\n  ║        THE HAUNTED CLUSTER                       ║\r\n  ║        A PostgreSQL Text Adventure               ║\r\n  ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\r\n\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\n  You wake up inside a dying PostgreSQL cluster.\r\n  The autovacuum hasn't run in months. Bloat is everywhere.\r\n  Find the Absent Daemon and restart it before the cluster falls.\r\n\r\n  Type 'help' for commands. Type 'quit' to escape.\r\n\r\n\r\n\u001b[38;5;15m\u001b[1m  The Lobby\r\n\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\n  Cracked marble floors, flickering fluorescent lights. Hundreds of connection requests queue at a rusted turnstile. An elephant statue in the corner is missing its trunk — someone chiseled it off years ago.\r\n  \r\n  Scrawled on the wall: 'NEVER run VACUUM FULL in production without testing. — 2019'\r\n\r\n  Exits: \u001b[38;5;14mnorth, east\r\n\u001b[0m  Items: \u001b[38;5;11mpg_dump scroll\r\n\u001b[0m  Enemies: \u001b[38;5;9mZombie Connection\r\n\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;14m  [Checkpoint — you will respawn here if you die]\r\n\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;14m  A small elephant trots past, muttering something about bloat. It disappears through the wall.\r\n\u001b[0m\r\n  > "]
