[18.071361, "o", "h"]
[18.148775, "o", "\r\n"]
[18.151956, "o", "\r\n\u001b[38;5;15m\u001b[1m  pgBouncer Antechamber\r\n\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\n  A narrow waiting room. Connections are pooled here before being allowed through. A sign reads: 'Max pool size: 100. Current: 100. Go away.'\r\n  \r\n  Elephant footprints in the dust lead north.\r\n\r\n  Exits: \u001b[38;5;14msouth, north\r\n\u001b[0m  Items: \u001b[38;5;11mDISCARD ALL scroll\r\n\u001b[0m  Enemies: \u001b[38;5;9mZombie Connection, Zombie Connection\r\n\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[38;5;14m  [PUZZLE]\r\n\u001b[0m\r\n  A panicked DBA ghost blocks your path.\r\n  \r\n  'Quick! My app is throwing connection errors. I have max_connections=100. What do I do?'\r\n  \r\n    a) Increase max_connections to 1000 and restart PostgreSQL\r\n    b) Deploy PgBouncer in transaction mode\r\n    c) Kill all idle connections with pg_terminate_backend\r\n\r\n  Your answer (a/b/c): "]
[20.462788, "o", "b"]
[20.548599, "o", "\r\n"]
[20.548676, "o", "\u001b[38;5;14m  CORRECT! The ghost relaxes. 'Connection pooling. Of course. You may pass.' It drops a key.\r\n\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;14m  You receive: Connection String Key\r\n\u001b[0m\r\n  > "]
